ns across 9 major irrigation project sites. Led contract labour management, grievance redressal, vendor management, and legal compliance. Senior Executive – HR & AdministrationAmrit Feeds Limited (Amrit Group of Companies), Patna, Bihar23rd February 2015 – 09th March 2016 Handled HR and IR activities, including union negotiations and employee welfare. Managed disciplinary procedures, recruitment, training, CSR, and conciliation processes. Officer – Personnel & AdministrationAFCONS Infrastructure LimitedChennai Metro Rail Project (CMRL), Shenoy Nagar to Thirumangalam Ramp, Chennai, Tamil Nadu01st July 2011 – 17th February 2015 Led IR/ER efforts for the underground metro project (5.17 km). Focused on statutory compliance, collective bargaining, layoffs, retrenchments, and welfare implementation. Admin Assistant – HR & AdministrationJMC Projects (India) LimitedBangalore Metro Rail Project (BMRL), Banashankari to Puttenhalli Station, Bangalore, Karnataka19th October 2010 – 28th June 2011 Managed site timekeeping, statutory registers (Muster Roll, Wage Sheet), lease agreements, and contractor bills. Supported employee relations, welfare, and labour compliance functions. Time Keeper – HR & AdminDLF Projects Limited15-Acre Residential Project, Rajarhat, Kolkata, West Bengal20th December 2007 – 18th October 2010 Maintained timekeeping, DLR reports, camp monitoring, and wage registers. Actively involved in labour relation activities and statutory compliance. Key Responsibilities: Industrial & Employee Relations: Managing all aspects of industrial and employee relations across the project site, including contract workforce management, coordination for factory and boiler licenses, environmental (pollution) certifications, and securing blasting permissions. Regulatory Compliance: Ensuring 100% statutory compliance with labour laws including CLRA, EPF, ESIC, EC Act, and other applicable legislations. Overseeing implementation of welfare schemes and employee compensation processes. Dispute & Conflict Resolution: Successfully managed over 10 major industrial actions such as strikes, gheraos, and picketing. Actively involved in wage negotiations and settlements under Section 18(1) and Section 12(3) of the Industrial Disputes Act. Handled and de-escalated violent protests involving large workforce groups (500+ workers). Disciplinary & Grievance Management: Leading grievance redressal mechanisms through formal committees. Managing disciplinary actions and addressing disputes through conciliation, adjudication, and arbitration processes. Contract Labour Management: Supervising and monitoring over 1,000 contract workers. Ensuring compliance with welfare provisions including sanitation, accommodation, restrooms, and potable water facilities. Manpower Planning & Budgeting: Strategic planning and allocation of manpower based on project requirements. Managing annual HR & Admin budgets, including manpower and operational expenses. Training & CSR Initiatives: Identifying training needs and conducting sessions on health, safety, and employee development. Organizing CSR programs such as plantation drives, safety weeks, and motivational activities. Administrative Management: Handling site administration, including canteen operations, hospitality, transport arrangements, guest house management, and security personnel supervision. Health & Safety Management: Spearheaded COVID-19 response at site including testing, isolation, and vaccination drives. Conducting regular health awareness and heatwave preparedness programs, along with periodic medical check-ups. MIS & Compliance Reporting: Maintaining statutory records and ensuring timely filing of returns. Preparing and updating MIS related to workforce deployment, compliance, audits, and budget utilization."}]'::jsonb, '[{"title":"Imported project details","description":"Managed a large-scale residential project with a budget of ₹780 crores. || Oversaw a workforce of 800, including 120 company staff, developin